HEADWORD: Ixia
<hw>Ix"i*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/
birdlime. So called because of the viscid nature of some of the
species.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A South African bulbous plant of
the Iris family, remarkable for the brilliancy of its flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ixobrychus</ent>⟦br⟧
